{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.32",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 32 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:1",
      "text": "And his three friends also ceased any longer to answer Job: for Job was righteous before them.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:2",
      "text": "Then Elius the son of Barachiel, the Buzite, of the kindred of Ram, of the country of Ausis, was angered: and he was very angry with Job, because he justified himself before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:3",
      "text": "And he was also very angry with his three friends, because they were not able to return answers to Job, yet set him down for an ungodly man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:4",
      "text": "But Elius had forborne to give an answer to Job, because they were older than he.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:5",
      "text": "And Elius saw that there was no answer in the mouth of the three men; and he was angered in his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:6",
      "text": "And Elius the Buzite the son of Barachiel answered and said, I am younger in age, and ye are elder, wherefore I kept silence, fearing to declare to you my own knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:7",
      "text": "And I said, It is not time that speaks, though in many years men know wisdom:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:8",
      "text": "but there is a spirit in mortals; and the inspiration of the Almighty is that which teaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:9",
      "text": "The long-lived are not wise as such; neither do the aged know judgement.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:10",
      "text": "Wherefore I said, Hear me, and I will tell you what I know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:11",
      "text": "Hearken to my words; for I will speak in your hearing, until ye shall have tried the matter with words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:12",
      "text": "and I shall understand as far as you; and, behold, there was no one of you that answered Job his words in argument,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:13",
      "text": "lest ye should say, We have found that we have added wisdom to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:14",
      "text": "And ye have commissioned a man to speak such words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:15",
      "text": "They were afraid, they answered no longer; they gave up their speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:16",
      "text": "I waited, (for I had not spoken,) because they stood still, they answered not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:17",
      "text": "And Elius continued, and said, I will again speak,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:18",
      "text": "for I am full of words, for the spirit of my belly destroys me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:19",
      "text": "And my belly is as a skin of sweet wine, bound up and ready to burst; or as a brazier’s labouring bellows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:20",
      "text": "I will speak, that I may open my lips and relieve myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:21",
      "text": "For truly I will not be awed because of man, nor indeed will I be confounded before a mortal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.32.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:22",
      "text": "For I know not how to respect persons: and if otherwise, even the moths would eat me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
